article.headline: Campbell beats Presbyterian 66-53
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Andrew Ryan scored 21 points, grabbed seven rebounds and had six assists to help Campbell beat Presbyterian 66-53 on Tuesday night. Ryan made five of Campbell's 10 3-pointers and Luke Moyer hit four more. Moyer had 14 points, D.J. Mason 13 and Reco McCarter added 12 for Campbell (9-15, 3-8 Big South). The Camels held a 31-20 advantage on the glass and had 20 assists on 25 field goals. Campbell held a 30-23 lead at halftime behind Mason's 11 points and Ryan's 10. DeSean Murray led Presbyterian (7-17, 3-8) with 17 points and six rebounds. Janeil Jenkins had 11 points and Jordan Downing 10. Murray pulled Presbyterian within 56-48 with 3:31 left but Moyer scored the next eight points, including consecutive 3-pointers for a 16-point lead -- Campbell's largest of the game.
